<br>
thus it's usually pretty difficult to do with anything at that point in the game less than close to full raid size (72 people). and to achieve that you obviously need a far bigger guild roster than that to make up for casual players, people who can't make it, etc. granted its a GREAT feeling when you finally do conquer something as difficult as that, and at times its actually kinda fun to watch such a huge force get stuff done, and i'm sure that in time it will require less and less people to accomplish, but it can be a pain in the arse to get that amount of people around, not to mention get them all geared up and ready to go. i am semi-glad that LDoN is lowering raid size, i would prefer to see well thought out, fun encounters with lower raid sizes, but a change like that has its own problems which i'd rather not bring up here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
in terms of the whole closeness thing, i personally know most of my guildies pretty well, and we field quite a large raid force at times, so i do believe it is possible to have large raids and still be pretty tight-knit. i do agree with delandril, though, that smaller raid sizes would probably help foster better guilds and happier players.  <p>Veteran Norok Zek<br>
