EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To me, this is what is more wrong with the &quot;end-game&quot; content.  There is a focus on a few classes but not opportunities for all of them, so a raid (and by extension raiding guild) is forced to be exclusionary, to exclude those who might want to participate.  On other servers that might not be as much of an issue because each player will generally have multiple characters on his/her account all close to the same level so they can just change to one that is needed mechanics-wise.  Mechanics is the god we really are trying to slay.<br>
<br>
Mechanics.... that's what has made the game 55+ a lot less fun for me.  Even the more RP oriented guilds and associations end up bowing to the &quot;god&quot; of mechanics once it gets 60+.  The amount of grinding (which is boring) one has to do to &quot;measure up&quot; is daunting and when the RP is gone or diminished, it jsut isn't worth it to me.  <br>
<br>
Heck...  I can even see why a raiding guild would not only accept but even desire ebayed characters because the player behind them handling the mechanics is what they are looking for and mechanics is all that one is buying with a &quot;toon&quot;.  I can also understand, on a mechanics level, why raiding guilds would even buy &quot;toons&quot; themselves to be botted or played by a member of the guild.  I can understand the mechanics reasons.<br>
<br>
Mechanics are what seperate and exclude in this game.  People have to work very hard not to let the mechanics overrule everything else... and it jsut doesn't work at some point. <p><center><table width="55%"><tr><td align="center">
