<br>
The noise, the action, people attacking with rage and courage, the running and screaming, the cries as they die, the thrill of victory when that big mother chicken slams into the ground.<br>
<br>
I found raiding to be challenging and very satisfying. Kudo's to the raid leaders who get these circuses all to the right spot and generally aimed at the right monster.<br>
<br>
I like the idea of a mix of smaller group challenges and the massive OMG we need a f*cking army to take that down. Both have their appeal and both have their pit falls but I would rather have both than just one or the other.<br>
<br>
On RP and raids, I think it is a wonderful time for opposing sides to interact while trying to achieve a common goal. It makes for the kind of story I would want to read. They fight with vigor against one another, they unite against the worse enemy, vanquish the monster(s) and then return to trying to kill each other again with hate and admiration of a worthy foe.<br>
<br>
Just my take on it and the possibilities it presents.<br>
